<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4693] column rename looses &apos;identity&apos; attribute.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4693</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;renaming an identity column causes the column to loose its &apos;identity&apos; attribute.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;you can reproduce the problem as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CREATE TABLE njr_version ( id INTEGER generated always as identity, databaseVersion INTEGER);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;insert into njr_version (databaseVersion) values (10);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8211; column inserted successfully.&lt;br/&gt;
rename column njr_version.id to idVersion;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;insert into njr_version (databaseVersion) values (10);&lt;br/&gt;
Error: Column &apos;IDVERSION&apos;  cannot accept a NULL value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To compound this problem there is no way to restore the renamed column&apos;s identity attribute as the alter command doesn&apos;t let you set an identity attribute. The only work around is to create a new table and copy the data across.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
