                            <comment id="12875897" author="knutanders" created="Sat, 5 Jun 2010 12:53:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug is present all the way back to the introduction of rename column in Derby 10.3, so I&apos;m updating affects versions to reflect that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cleared the fix version field since it is unknown when the bug will be fixed. Added the repro attached flag to indicate that the steps to reproduce are provided in the bug description.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12875924" author="bryanpendleton" created="Sat, 5 Jun 2010 20:07:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for tracking this problem down, Brett. It certainly appears&lt;br/&gt;
that RENAME COLUMN isn&apos;t maintaining the autoincrement&lt;br/&gt;
information properly. I&apos;ll see if I can fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12876050" author="bryanpendleton" created="Sun, 6 Jun 2010 16:59:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached &apos;patch.diff&apos; contains a proposed fix to the problem,&lt;br/&gt;
and a handful of regression tests. The essence of the fix&lt;br/&gt;
is to observe that, since RENAME COLUMN more-or-less&lt;br/&gt;
drops and re-adds the column, we need to ensure that when&lt;br/&gt;
the column is re-added, if it is an Autoincrement column, &lt;br/&gt;
we set the CREATE_AUTOINCREMENT flag that the parser&lt;br/&gt;
sets when initially creating the table.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regression tests completed successfully. Comments or&lt;br/&gt;
suggestions about the patch are welcome.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12878458" author="bryanpendleton" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2010 02:36:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to the trunk as revision 954344.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll investigate merging this fix back to the 10.6 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12878820" author="bryanpendleton" created="Tue, 15 Jun 2010 02:04:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged the fix to the 10.6 branch as revision 954684, and marked as resolved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
